<li>Spatial - where</li>
<li>Causality - implicit. </li>

<h2 id="Creativity">Creativity<a class="anchor-link" href="#Creativity">¶</a></h2><p><img alt="2019-07-25_11h10_59.png" src="data:image/png;base64, "/></p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<ul>
<li>Emergence: I draw a 3 lines, and a <strong>triangle emerges</strong> which was not there</li>
<li>Re-representation: When original representation is not conducive, we re represent. In analogical reasoning, if original re is earth rotates around the sun, and target has electron revolves the sun, we could change the former to suit</li>
<li>Serendipity: A problem in past is in suspended state, later suddenly from another experience a solution emerges for that. Eg: <strong>Velcro story</strong>. </li>
</ul>
<p>Also note <strong>some other</strong> is important. That is, there could be more processes of creativity.</p>
